{"title": "Guarding The Portal", "content": "There's some specific region of dimensional weirdness\u2014possibly a Hellgate, though it doesn't have to be malign. In any case, strange things regularly come out of it, or are attracted to it, and at least half of them are dangerous somehow. It's the job of Our Heroes to hang around near the weirdness, be all \"None Shall Pass\" if needed and deal with everything related to it. As a consequence, in serial works, it's the standard justification for the show's Monsters of the Week. The weirdness may have caused the surrounding area to become a City of Adventure.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GuardingThePortal", "media_links": ["https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/SonicTheHedgehogMegaManWorldsCollide", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheWheelOfTime", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheDresdenFiles", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CityOfBones2007", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BuffyTheVampireSlayer", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Torchwood", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekDeepSpaceNine", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateAtlantis", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Primeval", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsIVOblivion", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WorldOfWarcraft", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/WorldOfWarcraft", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/KingdomHearts", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheTrapDoor", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLifeAndTimesOfJuniperLee", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DannyPhantom", "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheRealGhostbusters"], "non_media_links": ["http